			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-951056">
									

<p>I personally loved the "chain restaurant as a memetic virus" angle, <em>especially since the word memetic doesn't even appear in the piece at all.</em> I am so pleased at this that I could be bouncing happily in my chair if the rest of the piece wasn't so horrifyingly profane. *shudder*</p>
<p>It strikes the right balance of juuuuust almost barely referencing some sort of Easter/Communion sort of ritual while being balls-out unholy… but not too obvious to make it look like another tired RELIGION! metaphor. Incredibly subtle for a story about cannibalism.</p>
<p>I was speechless on my first read through. So props to Chubert on this one.</p>

